books = [12, 34, 67, 90]
students = 2
Output: 113

Why Binary Search?
Minimum possible answer = max(pages[])
Maximum possible answer = sum(pages[])

🔹 Core Idea
  We guess a value (mid) = maximum pages a student can take
    Then check:“Is it possible to allocate books within this limit?”
  
  🔹 Steps (Algorithm)
    ✅ Step 1: Define search space
        low = max(pages)
        high = sum(pages)
    ✅ Step 2: Binary Search
        Repeat until low <= high:
        mid = (low + high) / 2
    Check feasibility:
        If possible → try smaller value → high = mid - 1
        If not → increase → low = mid + 1
🔹 Feasibility Function
      students_required = 1
      current_pages = 0
      
      for each book:
          if current_pages + book <= mid:
              add book
          else:
              students_required++
              current_pages = book
      
      if students_required <= m:
          feasible
      else:
          not feasible

public class AllocatePages {

    public static boolean isPossible(int[] arr, int n, int m, int mid) {
        int students = 1;
        int pages = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (arr[i] > mid) return false;

            if (pages + arr[i] <= mid) {
                pages += arr[i];
            } else {
                students++;
                pages = arr[i];
            }
        }

        return students <= m;
    }

    public static int findPages(int[] arr, int n, int m) {
        if (m > n) return -1;

        int low = 0, high = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            high += arr[i];
            low = Math.max(low, arr[i]);
        }

        int res = -1;

        while (low <= high) {
            int mid = (low + high) / 2;

            if (isPossible(arr, n, m, mid)) {
                res = mid;
                high = mid - 1;
            } else {
                low = mid + 1;
            }
        }

        return res;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {12, 34, 67, 90};
        int m = 2;

        System.out.println(findPages(arr, arr.length, m)); // 113
    }
}

Time Complexity
Binary Search: log(sum)
Feasibility check: O(n)

👉 Total: O(n log sum)
